canonical:
  title: 賀受徽號表
  author: 鄭文
  language: lzh
  text: 羣臣愛戴請上鴻名元聖聽從俾修盛禮照臨之內抃舞惟均中賀 皇帝克繼祖宗大開祚業能成德敎致悅服於邇遐載戢干戈保淸平於區宇政彰乃乂功協惟歌今則上承乾符下順人願擇靈辰而率典受寶冊以增休百神交欣以介岡陵之福萬邦畢湊爭陳玉帛之儀臣限守藩條阻參庭列仰美尊崇之事第深懽慶之悰
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 賀受徽號表
  author: 鄭文
  language: lzh
  text: 羣臣愛戴。請上鴻名。元聖聽從。俾修盛禮。照臨之內。抃舞惟均。中賀。 皇帝克繼祖宗。大開祚業。能成德敎。致悅服於邇遐。載戢干戈。保淸平於區宇。政彰乃乂。功協惟歌。今則上承乾符。下順人願。擇靈辰而率典。受寶冊以增休。百神交欣。以介岡陵之福。萬邦畢湊。爭陳玉帛之儀。臣限守藩條。阻參庭列。仰美尊崇之事。第深懽慶之悰。
korean:
  title: 휘호 받음을 하례하는 표
  author: 정문
  language: kor
  text: 뭇 신하들이 애모(愛慕)하고 추대(推戴)하여 큰 칭호를 올리고자 청하옴에 성군(聖君)께서 따라 주시어 성대한 예전(禮典)을 거행하게 되니, 온 누리가 다 같이 기뻐 춤추나이다. 중하(中賀) 황제께서 조종(祖宗)의 공덕을 이으시고 국조(國祚)와 제업(帝業)을 크게 열어, 성덕과 교화로써 원근(遠近)을 모두 열복(悅服)하게 하시며 간과(干戈)를 거두어 온 누리의 태평을 보전하시니, 정치가 잘 성취되어 그 공덕을 만민이 구가(謳歌)하나이다.이제 위로 하늘의 상서를 받고 아래로 만 백성의 소원에 맞추시어, 길일(吉日)을 택하여 의식을 거행하고 보책(寶冊)을 받으시어 경복(慶福)을 더하시니, 백신(百神)이 모두 기뻐 강릉(岡陵)의 복을 빌고 만방(萬邦)이 다 모여 옥백(玉帛)의 예물을 다투어 올리나이다.신(臣)은 번직(藩職)에 구애되어 조회하는 반열에 참석하지 못하오나, 우러러 존숭(尊崇)하는 성사(盛事)를 기리고 충심으로 환경(歡慶)의 뜻을 표하나이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0340_010_0230&viewSync=OT
  footnotes:
  - key: '[주-D001] 강릉(岡陵)의 복을 빌고 : '
    value: 《시경》에, “뫼와 같고 언덕과 같으라[如岡如陵].”는 구절이 있는데, 오래 살기를 축원하는 시다.
english:
  title: Memorial Presenting Congratulations on the Receipt of an Imperial Honorific
  author: Jeong Mun
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The assembled ministers, devoted and reverent, petition to bestow upon you a great name. The sage ruler graciously accedes, that the magnificent ceremonies might be performed. Throughout all that is illuminated and ruled, all dance in unified joy.

    In the central commendation: The Emperor succeeds to the virtue of ancestors and forebears, opening widely the fortune and enterprises of the dynasty. Through the cultivation of noble character and transformative teaching, he brings delight and submission from near and far. Having sheathed the weapons of war, he preserves the peace and clarity across the realm. His governance achieves its fullness; his merit becomes the song of ten thousand voices.

    Now, receiving from above the auspicious signs of Heaven, and responding below to the desires of the people, he selects an auspicious day to conduct the rites in proper form, receiving the sacred register to augment his blessed fortune. The hundred spirits rejoice together, beseeching the blessings that endure like mountains and hills. The ten thousand lands gather as one, vying to present the ritual offerings of jade and silk.

    Though I am confined within my provincial station, prevented from taking my place in the assembly of court, I gaze upward in admiration at this magnificent achievement, and in all sincerity express the joy and celebration that fills my heart.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The phrase 'blessings that endure like mountains and hills' is drawn from the *Book of Songs* and expresses the wish for longevity and lasting prosperity.
